Two people were arrested after they returned to a restaurant in Hout Bay to pick up their forgotten bag of rhino horn and ivory. CAPE TOWN - Two people have been arrested after they forgot their loot of rhino horn and ivory at a restaurant in Hout Bay.The pair returned to the eatery on Monday to pick up a backpack they d left there on Sunday.The Hawks' Lloyd Ramovha says by that stage staff had already alerted authorities. The seemingly oblivious pair were directed to the nearby police station, where the parcel was said to be handed in for safekeeping. The loot is valued at just over R60,000. &quot;Upon their arrival, members of the elite unit were alert and the two were arrested on the spot. The two suspects are due to appear in the Wynberg Magistrates Court on Wednesday.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)